Someone asked me to demonstrate how observance of #Torah is greater than sacrifice, so I said ok, let's look at the language:

The word for #commandments in Hebrew is Mitzvot מצות, which comes from the root Tzevah צוה which literally means to #bind or #attach. 
The word for offerings in Hebrew is #Qorban קרבן which comes from the word #Qarev קרב and it literally means to "#draw #near". Each #commandment literally binds or attaches us to #TheAlmighty while an #offering draws us nearer to Him. While drawing near to God is Great, it will #NEVER #EVER trump binding or attaching yourself to Him (613 Torah)!

When the mind is silenced the yogi enters into the thoughtless state or Asamprajnata Samadhi.
-I am not the mind, body, nor the senses. - 🕉💜🙌🏻

Just got a #yaksant #tattoo at #WatBangPhra temple located outside of #Bangkok. The monks were awesome. They use a long metal rod called a #KhemSak to pierce the skin and create the tattoo. Before you start, you give them an #offering #basket, then they #pray over it and you to receive words that they will put on the tattoo for each individual person.

Then I visited the Master #Shaolin who prayed over the tattoo to give it a #blessing and sealed it by rubbing #gold flakes into the tattoo. 
Been an awesome day 😁#international #travel #randr #tattooedmilitary

There are some moments we never forget. This day in a village along the flanks of the active volcano, Mount Agung, was one such moments. Painful, poetic. Spiritual and at times, heart wrenching, I was left deeply effected by this ceremony. Layers of fear we harbor within the mind, brought forward when witnessing the intensity a life before us.
- 
Caption ~ Men of the Bali Aga or who are considered the original inhabitants of Bali, parade through their village a sacred cow prior to the Usaba Kawulu Ceremony for the ritual know as the Pecaruan Tabuh Rah Banteng (or sacrificing a sacred bull) in Asak Kangin village located near Mount Agung on the island of Bali, Indonesia. The ceremony, held once a year, is dedicated to Ida Betara ring Puseh Nyoman (the spiritual god which resides in Puseh Nyoman temple). Using axes, the bull will chased by nearly 100 men and sacrificed, its blood poured all across the village while attempting to run from the sharp blades, a sacred event believed to receive a blessing of prosperity and ward evil for the community that resides next to Gunung Agung, the most spiritual volcano in Bali.
-
From the archive, Volcano Gods story for National Geographic.

The #transition from #childhood to #manhood for the #manchild Is serious business. If you only knew how much I've had to simply just send this young man #goodenergy and trust that he will find his way back home. 🙏🏽
If you only knew about the many #sleeplessnights watching my phone and the time hoping that he just arrives back safely. 🙏🏽
If you only knew the #heartaches And #stress of raising a #teenageboy into a #man 🙏🏽
If I could only tell you the story and the journey of having to push through all of my work, running my businesses, working through the #agony of not knowing if he'd return home. #ifyouonlyknew 😫
If you only knew.....yes I will write about it in my upcoming book #ownit launching hopefully this Fall. 
And so today he #returns with so much #love for his #mother. 
As parents especially mothers we must always remember to keep our #heart open to give love even during difficult times. It's the love that will always bring them back home. 
This is the greatest gift that a mother could ever experience....when her child returns home with love, respect, and honor for his mother. My tears were felt and Prayers answered. 🙏🏽🔮🙏🏽
#happymothersday #mother #queenmother #returnhome #teenager #ilovemychildren

Tapi apa memang persahabatan bisa kendur karena jarak? Aku yakin inti persahabatan tentu tidak rusak tapi jarak dan tempat tidak bisa berdusta, berpisah secara fisik bisa merenggangkan keintiman persahabatan karena tidak lagi disirami oleh pertemuan, canda, dan diskusi. (Ahmad Fuadi. Rana Tiga Warna)

Persahabatan itu seumpama laut dan pasir, senantiasa bersama-sama menghadapi pecahan ombak, bersama-sama merasakan lelehan senja, dan saling melengkapi dari masa ke masa. (Aiman Bagea. Ketika Saat Cinta Bersilangan)

Hal itu sangat membantu baiknya moral dan intelektual manusia, dalam sebuah persahabatan dengan orang-orang yang berbeda dengan dirinya, yang tidak terlalu peduli terhadap cita-citanya, dimana ia harus menunjukkan siapa dirinya lewat kemampuannya. (Nathaniel Hawthorne)
